ficiency","Radioactive iodine therapy","Hashimoto thyroiditis","Congenital thyroid dysgenesis"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESecondary hypothyroidism develops when the anterior pituitary fails to produce adequate TSH. A \u003Cstrong\u003Epituitary macroadenoma\u003C/strong\u003E can physically compress and impair normal pituitary tissue function, disrupting TSH production and leading to thyroid hormone deficiency.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other conditions listed cause primary hypothyroidism through direct effects on the thyroid gland:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDietary iodine deficiency\u003C/strong\u003E prevents the thyroid from synthesising adequate thyroid hormones\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERadioactive iodine therapy\u003C/strong\u003E causes targeted destruction of thyroid follicular cells\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHashimoto thyroiditis\u003C/strong\u003E involves immune-mediated inflammation and destruction of thyroid tissue\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECongenital thyroid dysgenesis\u003C/strong\u003E represents incomplete or abnormal thyroid gland formation during development\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELaboratory findings in secondary hypothyroidism typically show low TSH levels alongside low thyroid hormones. This pattern differs from primary hypothyroidism where TSH levels are elevated due to impaired negative feedback from low circulating thyroid hormones.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Primary hypothyroidism results from thyroid gland dysfunction while secondary hypothyroidism stems from inadequate pituitary TSH production.","Secondary hypothyroidism shows concurrent low TSH and low thyroid hormone levels.","Pituitary disorders including tumours, trauma, and inflammation can cause secondary hypothyroidism."],"references":["Chaker L, Bianco AC, Jonklaas J, Peeters RP. Hypothyroidism. Lancet. 2017 Sep 23;390(10101):1550-1562. doi: 10.1016/S0140-6736(17)30703-1. Epub 2017 Mar 20. PMID: 28336049; PMCID: PMC6619426.","Patil N, Rehman A, Anastasopoulou C, et al. Hypothyroidism. [Updated 2024 Feb 18]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK519536/","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55844"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15584"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55844","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55844"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-14T20:12:12+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-14T20:13:09+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8275"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70380"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","i